The method should return a string representing the lexicographically smallest instructions that will lead Bob to the `destination`.
The returned string should consist of only the characters 'H' and 'V'.
The length of the returned string should be equal to the sum of the values in the `destination` array.
The returned string should be one of the valid instructions that will lead Bob to the `destination`.
The returned string should be the `k`th lexicographically smallest instruction.
